I have been making this cake for years (it is in the NY Times Jewish Cookbook) but you must use a tube- type pan or the center will not cook. I use a removable bottom angel food pan with straight sides. I also chop the apples into about half inch chunks and do the cake in three layers, alternating apples and batter and ending with batter. I have also used prune plums, which work just as well. Note, the batter is STICKY, but don't worry about it. One final suggestion: Try using a quality olive oil instead of a neutral oil. It adds an interesting note.

